{"type":null,"faqId":36224,"title":"How can I reduce mobile data usage?","answer":"<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 106.3pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>Connect to a Wi-Fi network if there is one available.</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 106.3pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>Turn off the mobile data connection when you are not using\nmobile data.</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 106.3pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>When browsing web pages, you can prevent images from loading on\nthe page if you do not need to view them.</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char;'>In the <b>Browser</b>\ninterface, open the options menu, select <b>Settings\n&gt; Bandwidth management</b> and deselect <b>Load\nimages</b>.</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 106.3pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>Disable background data syncing if not needed.</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char;'>Swipe downwards from the status bar to display shortcut\nswitches and then touch <img width=\"29\" height=\"21\" src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=SupportImage&imagePath=/20150805152440148001.gif\"><span>&nbsp;</span>to turn off\nthe auto sync function.</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 106.3pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>Close the apps that you are not using.</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char;'>Open the list of recently-used apps and close the apps\nthat you are no longer using.</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 106.3pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>Stop apps in the background from accessing the Internet via\nmobile data.</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char;'>Go to <b>Settings</b>\nand select <b>Networked apps</b>. Then\nselect the apps for which you want to restrict Internet access and turn off the\ncorresponding mobile data switch.</p>","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":3,"unUseful":0,"languageId":1,"languageName":"en","faqCode":"1249","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"1","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1438759485000,"seriesProductName":"","visitedTimes":48,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"mobile data usage; data usage","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}